=== 印度 ===
2008年，印度議會未經辯論就通過了《信息技術法案》，賦予政府法定權力，無需法院命令或搜查令即可竊聽所有通信。該法案第 69 條規定︰「在為了印度的主權完整、保衛印度、國家安全、公共秩序、防止煽動實施任何可識別的犯罪或調查任何罪行時，第69條授權中央政府/州政府/其授權機構在必要或適當的情況下攔截、監控或解密任何儲存在電腦裡的信息。」<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/all-computers-can-now-be-monitored-by-govt-agencies/article25792523.ece|title=All computers can now be monitored by govt. agencies|date=2018-12-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-12-27|others=Special Correspondent|language=en|issn=0971-751X|archive-date=2022-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220416091941/https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/all-computers-can-now-be-monitored-by-govt-agencies/article25792523.ece}}</ref>

印度正在建立一個名為NATGRID的國家情報網，<ref>[http://pib.nic.in/release/release.asp?relid=54679 "Centralised System to Monitor Communications"] {{Wayback|url=http://pib.nic.in/release/release.asp?relid=54679 |date=20181027233840 }}, reply by Shri [[Gurudas_Kamat|Gurudas Kamat]], [[Minister_of_State_for_Communications_and_Information_Technology|Minister of State for Communications and Information Technology]] in [[Rajya_Sabha|Rajya Sabha]], [[Press_Information_Bureau|Press Information Bureau]], 26 November 2009. Retrieved 17 September 2013.</ref>該網將於2011年5月全面建成，每個印度人的數據包括土地記錄、互聯網日誌、航空和鐵路 PNR、電話記錄、槍支記錄、駕駛執照、財產記錄及保險都被實時監視，情報網不受監督。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/MHA-to-make-security-data-tamper-free/articleshow/5078546.cms|work=[[The_Times_of_India|The Times of India]]|first1=Vishwa|last1=Mohan|agency=[[Times_News_Network|TNN]]|title=MHA to make security data tamper-free|date=2 October 2009|access-date=17 September 2013|archive-date=2016-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215223924/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/MHA-to-make-security-data-tamper-free/articleshow/5078546.cms}}</ref>從2011年2月起，印度唯一身份驗證機構向每個印度人提供了一個 UID，政府因此將能夠實時跟踪人們。另外2011年人口普查建立所有公民的全國人口登記冊，在此期間將採集指紋和虹膜掃描以及每個家庭的GPS記錄。<ref>[http://www.igovernment.in/site/india-to-prepare-npr-with-2011-census/ India to prepare NPR with 2011 Census] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905052217/http://www.igovernment.in/site/india-to-prepare-npr-with-2011-census/|date=5 September 2012}}, iGovernment (9.9 Mediaworx), 24 April 2008. Retrieved 17 September 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.rediff.com/news/2008/aug/25ec.htm "Election Commission to use Census data, GPS to track voters"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/2008/aug/25ec.htm |date=20201130055130 }}, [[Rediff|Rediff]] (Delhi), 25 August 2008. Retrieved 17 September 2012.</ref>

印度的幾個州已經安裝了具有面部匹配功能的閉路電視監控系統，該系統使用生物識別技術。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Right to privacy: Data shows states using Aadhaar to build profiles of citizens|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/despite-govt-denials-states-building-databases-for-360-degree-profiles-of-citizens/story-qnSLHGyZIXiZiO4ce84UuO.html|date=25 August 2017|access-date=2022-04-16|archive-date=2021-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210716114740/https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/despite-govt-denials-states-building-databases-for-360-degree-profiles-of-citizens/story-qnSLHGyZIXiZiO4ce84UuO.html}}</ref>

=== 馬來西亞 ===
2018 年 7 月，馬來西亞警方宣布成立馬來西亞攔截兒童犯罪單位（icacu），該單位配備在美國開發的實時大規模互聯網監控軟件，負責監控所有馬來西亞互聯網用戶，借此打擊兒童色情。該系統創建了一個用戶數據庫，其中包括 IP 地址、網站、位置、使用時間和頻率以及上傳和下載的文件等詳細信息。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Watching porn? Cops now have their eyes on you | Malay Mail|url=https://www.malaymail.com/s/1650214/watching-porn-cops-now-have-their-eyes-on-you|access-date=2022-04-16|archive-date=2019-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190113110545/https://www.malaymail.com/s/1650214/watching-porn-cops-now-have-their-eyes-on-you}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=[Exclusive] Police will know if you watch porn|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/exclusive/2018/07/388926/exclusive-police-will-know-if-you-watch-porn|date=9 July 2018|access-date=2022-04-16|archive-date=2019-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929182547/https://www.nst.com.my/news/exclusive/2018/07/388926/exclusive-police-will-know-if-you-watch-porn}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Respect privacy and no to monitoring of internet usage or activity in Malaysia, say ASEAN NGOs|url=https://www.theonlinecitizen.com/2018/07/20/respect-privacy-and-no-to-monitoring-of-internet-usage-or-activity-in-malaysia-say-asean-ngos/|access-date=16 August 2018|date=20 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920221800/https://www.theonlinecitizen.com/2018/07/20/respect-privacy-and-no-to-monitoring-of-internet-usage-or-activity-in-malaysia-say-asean-ngos/|archive-date=20 September 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== 荷蘭 ===
根據 2004 年的一份報告，如果按人均計算，荷蘭政府進行的秘密竊聽和攔截比世界上任何國家都多。<ref name="Italy and the Netherlands top wiretaps chart. EDRi-gram 15 July 2004 from EDRI.org">[https://edri.org/edrigramnumber2-14wiretap/ "Italy and the Netherlands top wiretap chart"] {{Wayback|url=https://edri.org/edrigramnumber2-14wiretap/ |date=20190507031920 }}, Digital Civil Rights in Europe, EDRI-gram Number 2.14, 15 July 2004. Retrieved 17 September 2013.</ref>荷蘭軍事情報局 MIVD 運營一個衛星地面站來攔截外國衛星鏈路，同時也是一個竊聽外國高頻無線電通信的設施。荷蘭企業進行大規模監控的一個例子是由五家荷蘭銀行（ABN AMRO、ING、Rabobank、Triodos Bank 和 de Volksbank）所發起的一項倡議。2020 年 7 月，這五家銀行決定建立荷蘭交易監控 (TMNL)，共同打擊洗錢和恐怖主義融資。 TMNL 的目標是將荷蘭銀行提供的所有交易信息收集到一個中央數據庫中，以實現全面的集體交易監控。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nvb.nl/english/transaction-monitoring-netherlands-a-unique-step-in-the-fight-against-money-laundering-and-the-financing-of-terrorism/ |title="Press release of The Dutch Banking Association, 8 July 2020" |access-date=2022-04-16 |archive-date=2022-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220319081322/https://www.nvb.nl/english/transaction-monitoring-netherlands-a-unique-step-in-the-fight-against-money-laundering-and-the-financing-of-terrorism/ }}</ref>

=== 新加坡 ===
新加坡的監控十分廣泛，包括公共區域的閉路電視、互聯網監控、交通監控以及監控元數據等。<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|url=https://www.techinasia.com/singapore-advanced-surveillance-state-citizens-mind|access-date=2022-04-16|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109124407/https://www.techinasia.com/singapore-advanced-surveillance-state-citizens-mind}}</ref>新加坡政府有權訪問通信數據，當地最大的電信公司 Singtel 與政府關係密切，並且新加坡法律允許政府在無需法院許可的情況下從其人民那裡獲取敏感數據，例如短信、電子郵件、通話記錄和網上歷史記錄。<ref name="#1"/>

